originalText.text:
I had a suit cleaned at Rosa's that I needed for an important work trip. I delivered the suit well in advance and was surprised that the it would take almost 6 days to clean and triple-checked with the representative that the suit would be ready by noon of the pick-up date because the work event was so important, which they confirmed. I would have taken the suit elsewhere if they did assure me the suit would be ready by a certain time.

When I went to pick-up the suit, it was not ready and are not being accountable to it being late. Now I need to buy a new suit for the event.

originalText.text:
This review was long overdue.

Last summer when I first moved to the neighborhood, and I was using google to find the dry cleaner. I came across this business. I dropped off my clothes and a blanket. When I picked up, there was one dress missing. This lady kept telling me come back next day, then next week. Back and forth for several times. Finally, she said Michael will call you. Michael never call. So I said did you lost my dress? It is ok to tell me. One thing let to another I had to travel for awhile. Then I came and I gave it one more try. Then she said did Michael call you? I said nobody called me. Then she called this person assumed to be Michael, and he said he did not see any dress. She then asked me if I went to MexicoðŸ˜€ I was like what? I did not go to Mexico. After 20 minutes and it was my last attempt, I finally gave up and before i walked out I only said itâ€™s ok to tell me that you lost my dress.

So if you decided to use this business, make sure to take pictures of all your clothes.

originalText.text: Really nice staff. Reasonable price to dry clean a jacket and they reattached a button to my pants for free. They also gave me a new coat hanger because the one I was using was lousy.

originalText.text: I take all of my suits, shirts, and trousers here for cleaning. Very good value and pretty quick turnaround. I haven't had alternations done here so can't speak to that.
